title: For Sale:  Gustloff Werke Suhl KKW German .22
postcontent: The K. K. Wehrsportgewehr rifles were the standard pre-war training rifles used by the German military and were intended to duplicate the weight and feel of the standard K98 rifle. The top of the receiver ring is marked with a block "G" logo over "GUSTLOFF-WERKE / Waffenwerk-Suhl." The right side of the receiver is marked " KK. WEHRSPORTGEWEHR," and the left side of the barrel is marked "KAL 22 LANGE FUR BUCHSEN", followed by the serial number and the "eagle/N" proofmark. The "eagle / N" is also marked on the left side of the receiver. The stock is a European walnut with two barrel bands, handguard, bayonet lug, sling swivels, leather sling, and steel buttplate. It has a military style tangent rear sight graduated to 200 meters. Excellent. 90-95% of the original blue finish remains. The stock and handguard are both very fine and have minor dings and scratches. The handguard has a slight crack in the wood. The action functions fine, and the markings are crisp.This is a very collectible rifle and even though thousands were made they are very scarce. This rifle would be perfect for any true K98 or German military collector. If you have any questions please feel free to ask.

That being said I would sell this outright for (was $1600) now $1375 shipped to your FFL, preferably paid with a USPS MO.  Rifle will ship to your FFL once money order(s) have been cashed/cleared to confrm authenticity. I am open to other trade offers but my goal is to get the Legion 10mm so any other trades would have to be mostly cash and closer to my build value because I would just be reselling any trade items in order to get the 10mm, but feel free to shoot me an offer if you've got something in mind.  For this one I'm not looking for any types of ARs/rifles or shotguns, mainly just the few trades mentioned below.--- Here is the complete build list but if I'm forgetting anything just shoot me an email and I can fill in the details. Lower Parts:•AXTS AX556 Full-Ambi Billet Lower Receiver - Cerakoted in Tungsten •P.O.F. Patriot Ordnance Factory 3.5lb Flat Drop-in Trigger •B.A.D.A.S.S. title: For Sale:  Hopkins & Allen 16GA Shotgun, pre 1910
postcontent: This is a 16GA Hopkins & Allen single barrel break open shotgun. Hopkins and Allen were in business from 1896 to 1915. This shotgun is marked "Hopkins & Allen Arms Company Norwich Conn USA" which puts it after 1898, and it has a 4 digit serial number, 6687, which puts it probably before 1910. The stock is nice hardwood with a 4 digit number (not matching), refinished with what appears to be poly.The barrel is marked "Full Choked" on top of it, and its a liquid steel barrel (i.e. not weak thin Damascus).  Not very many of those in a functioning condition out there... There's some pitting on the buttplate and some dings here and there but other than that its pretty decent, no rust on barrel or receiver. At some point in its life it was refinished but there is still some brown patina on it.Cheap simple shotgun. 16 GA = power of a 12GA with a kick of a 20GA. Additional pics on request. Asking $120. Willing to ship to your FFL.Took it out to the farm to test fire. The gun shoots and extracts the cartrige without any issues. The kick is VERY tame. This would make a great "throw it in the truck" shotgun for "just in case".

title: For Sale:  Genuine MRE's
postcontent: These are genuine mil-spec MRE's, not the cheap commercial wanna-be "camping meals".  There are two different cases (Case A and Case B).  Each case has a different assortment of 12 meals.  With 12 meals per case, at this price, it is only $4.58 a meal for food that you can take anywhere with no refrigeration and still have a hot meal with loads of accessories such as crackers/bread, cheese/jelly spread, coffee, sugar, creamer, gum, Tabasco sauce, matches, and even toilet paper!  These come with a water-activated heater for the entree, and detailed directions on how to use it.  I also have spare heaters that I will provide so that you can heat up accessories as well.  The dates on the boxes are the Re-inspect Date, not the expiration date.  Genuine MRE cases like these have a TTI (Time and Temperature Indicator) on the outside of the box to assist inspectors in determining if MREs are still good. There are two parts to the TTI – an outer dark circle and an inner light circle. As long as the inner circle is still lighter than the outside circle, the MREs are good.  Shown here is a picture of the actual TTI from one of the cases (and they all look like this).  As you can see, the center is much lighter than the Reference Ring, indicating that these case still have a lot of life left in them.  $55 per case or only $50 per case if you buy two or more cases.THESE ARE LEGAL TO OWN, so please don't be an internet lawyer and try to enforce a law that doesn't exist.

title: For Sale:  Vintage S&W Chief's Special .38 Spl. Model 36 Revolver
postcontent:
This is one of the Smith & Wesson's true classic revolvers; not a re-introduction. Owned by the same person since new; now deceased. The cylinder rotation wear ring is barely visible, indicating very few rounds fired through it. Blueing is dark and deep with no pitting, wear, rust, or patina. Checkered diamond grips with S&W Medallion inset have no scratches or wear either. Was never holstered.
Smith & Wesson made the Model 36 Revolver to enable the use of the more powerful .38 Special ammunition in the smaller J-Frame concealable package. This revolver is serial numbered 338XXX which dates the manufacture anywhere from 1962 until 1965. It features the flat latch cylinder release, swing out cylinder, pinned barrel, exposed hammer, three screw frame, all steel material, and dark wood grips The 5 round capacity cylinder and 1.875" barrel make this J-Frame a very desireable carry handgun. BONUS ! Face to face sale will come with three boxes of ammunition.
Like so many firearms; this revolver is a true part of firearms history and is in the condition that you would be proud to show. Wish I could afford to keep it. C&R eligible.
